St Henry’s Marist College recently awarded the schools maintenance supervisor, Albert Cele with a long service award. Cele has worked at the school for 50 years since 1970 and according to the school this is extremely rare. Cele was presented with a special blazer to commemorate the momentous occasion. KerryAnne Francis, marketing, admissions and events manager at St Henry’s said: “Having had Cele at the college for so long epitomizes his character and unwavering loyalty to the College.” She said that the award presentation assembly was also the ideal opportunity to celebrate his recent birthday with a cake and have “Happy Birthday” sung to him by all who were present to witness the special moment. “Thank you Albert Cele – you are a “TrueBlue” and a Marist Gentleman through and through,” said Francis.